OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Sat 18 Jul to Mon 27 Jul
OL,6,FHigh pressure is likely to remain
OL,7,Fclose to the UK into this period, and
OL,8,Flikely centred to the west or
OL,9,Fnorthwest of the country. This means
OL,10,Fplenty more dry weather for most if
OL,11,Fnot all parts, though with the source
OL,12,Fregion of the air being the North
OL,13,FAtlantic, somewhat cooler, or at least
OL,14,Fless hot, conditions are expected,
OL,15,Fcompared to many recent days. Towards
OL,16,Fthe latter part of July, the influence
OL,17,Fof high pressure may wane somewhat,
OL,18,Fallowing a greater chance of rain,
OL,19,Fshowers or thunderstorms compared to
OL,20,Fearlier in the month. Overall,
OL,21,Ftemperatures are expected to remain
OL,22,Fabove average during this period.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
